I Spent $100 on This Brunch So You Donâ€™t Have To!!
Brunch at Crown Block in Dallas had been on my radar for weeks. So I went there for my first brunch in 2025â€¼ï¸
But after spending $100 on this meal, Iâ€™m here to say: itâ€™s not worth itğŸ’”
The view. No question, the skyline from Crown Block is breathtaking and probably one of the best in the city ğŸ™ï¸
The ambiance is polished, and itâ€™s clear theyâ€™ve aimed to create a high-end experience.
Now for the food. You get only one main course, and all other food is buffet-style. For $80 per person, tbh, I expected way more. The buffet offerings were limited to steak/ham, sushi and dessert, and let me just say, the desserts didnâ€™t impress. The macarons? They honestly tasted like they came straight from Costco[å¤±æœ›R]
So, if youâ€™re considering Crown Block for your next brunch outing, think twice[å¯æ€œR]
